<paragraph blockId="11.[112,647,215,398]" pageId="11" pageNumber="676">
The new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1894" class="Arachnida" family="Hormuridae" genus="Opisthacanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="676">O. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other Malagasy species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1861" box="[506,647,241,265]" class="Arachnida" family="Hormuridae" genus="Opisthacanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,647,241,265]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="676">Opisthacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: 1) a very much paler general coloration; 2) reduction of the median and lateral eyes of about 25% of their size; and 3) hemispermatophore with the distal lamina shorter than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1894" box="[463,646,347,371]" class="Arachnida" family="Hormuridae" genus="Opisthacanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis box="[463,646,347,371]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="676">O. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not as enlarged.
</paragraph>
